title.narrative: Accelerated HIV Control Program to end the AIDS epidemic in Senegal by 2030

description.narrative: Senegal - HIV - Conseil National de Lutte contre le SIDA de la République du Sénégal - CNLS. This program has the following goals: Halve new HIV infections. Improving the quality of life of those infected and affected by HIV and 50% reduction in AIDS-related deaths. The objectives of this program are: At least 70% of populations in vulnerability context adopt safer behaviors 2017. At least 30% of the general population did their testing and know their status over the last 12 months by 2017. At least 85% of the exposed key populations (SW, MSM, IDU) adopt a lower risk behavior 2017. At least 90% of HIV-positive pregnant women receive the package of services to reduce the risk of HIV transmission from mother to child by 2017. At least 85% of children and adults living with HIV receive comprehensive medical care by 2017
